This paper deals with coordination and bargaining between selfish users over a communication channel, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and game theory (cs.GT). The interference channel is a type of networked system, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses optimization problems and dynamic bargaining games, which are relevant to control systems (cs.SY) and multimedia systems (cs.MM).
